# Change Documentation

This rule applies only inside this repository. Do not treat it as a global preference for other projects unless the user explicitly asks for the same rule there.

Create or update a Markdown file in the root `docs/` folder after each major change or meaningful update.

- Use `docs/` at the repository root.
- Create concise `.md` files with clear names like `docs/auth-update.md` or `docs/invoice-flow.md`.
- Include what changed, why it changed, and any setup, migration, or follow-up notes.
- Update an existing related doc instead of creating duplicates when that is cleaner.

## Example

```markdown
# Invoice Update

## What Changed
- Added invoice status validation.

## Why
- Prevent invalid transitions in checkout flows.
```
